# Cloudflare Pages redirects — mirrors what netlify.toml used to do,
# minus the cross-origin API proxies (Pages `_redirects` only supports
# same-site proxying; external hosts silently fall through to the SPA
# fallback). Cross-origin proxies live as Pages Functions:
#   /api/rt/<feed>/<endpoint>  →  functions/api/rt/[feed]/[[endpoint]].js
#   /api/tranzy/<path>         →  functions/api/tranzy/[[path]].js
# Functions run before this file so their routes win.
# Docs: https://developers.cloudflare.com/pages/configuration/redirects/

# SPA fallback for client-side routing (SvelteKit outputs index.html
# from adapter-static). Must be last.
/*                         /index.html                                200
